<answer-choice correct="yes">         Marine biologists do not believe there
are isolated populations of monk seals</answer-choice>
<answer-choice>          Marine biologists hope science will find a way to
restore the monk seal population.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice>          Marine biologists feel the time has come for frank
discussion about pollution in the Caribbean.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice>          Marine biologists think isolated islands in the Caribbean
offer the best chance of finding populations of monk seals.</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true" hide="yes">
<para>          The function of the idiomatic expression <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> wishful
thinking </emphasis>is to show that what is desired is impossible, or at least
improbable, to achieve; therefore, marine biologists do not believe that they
exist. <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> Hopes, </emphasis>unlike wishes,
indicate possibilities (B). <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> Frank discussions </emphasis>(C)
and <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> offer the best chance </emphasis>(D)
have nothing to do with the original statement.</para>
</explanation>
